result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Wayne Briggs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: 02:05 PM/Rm. 301/Defendant Tyler Wayne Briggs in court with attorney John Zich.  Defendant Tyler Wayne Briggs in custody.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Reporter by Zoom.  Plea agreement.  Amended information filed, copy to Def.'s Atty.  Ct. 1 amended to 2nd degree recklessly endangering safety as repeater -  941.30(2), G felony, repeater.  On plea to Ct. 1 as amended, dismiss & read in Cts. 2 and 3.  Joint recommendation:  18 months initial confinement, 24 months extended supervision, consecutive to any other sentence, costs, DNA sample & surcharge, no contact with officer victim except in officer capacity, no contact with officer, AODA & follow through with treatment recommendations, maintain absolute sobriety, counseling as deemed necessary by agent.  Def.'s Atty. has received a copy of amended information and waives its reading.  Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights form filed with Court.  Court reviews with Def. Court advises Def. of constitutional rights and right to jury trial.  Def. waives rights and jury trial.  Court advises Def. of elements and penalties.  Def. advised of possible deportation if not US citizen.  Court finds plea entered freely and voluntarily.  Factual basis.  Court accepts plea and finds Def. guilty of Ct. 1 - 2nd degree recklessly endangering safety as repeater.  Sentencing remarks by State.  Victim rights complied with.  Sentencing remarks by Def.'s Atty.  Def. makes statement to Court.  Court orders 3 1/2 years prison, 1 1/2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision, consecutive to any other sentence, costs, DNA sample if not already done and surcharge, no contact with officer victim except in officer's capacity, no contact with officer victim's residence, AODA & follow through with recommendations at discretion of agent, maintain absolute sobriety, counseling as deemed necessary by agent.  Def. is eligible for the Earned Release and Challenge Incarceration Programs.  Credit 0.  Def. advised of voting and firearm rights.  Def. advised of postconviction rights.
